org.unbunt.ella.lang
Class NReal

java.lang.Object
  org.unbunt.ella.engine.corelang.AbstractObj
      org.unbunt.ella.lang.NReal
All Implemented Interfaces:
Obj, NNumeric
public class NReal
extends AbstractObj
implements NNumeric

Represents an EllaScript object wrapping a double value. NOTE: We do not implement special script objects to represent double's special values like NaN and infinity. Instead we rely on Java's native handling of these values on operations with values of other types and in case of operations involving BigInteger and BigDecimal we handle the errors provoked by such operations and follow the Java principle that any operation involving NaN will result in NaN extending this principle to also apply for operations involving BigInteger or BigDecimal and one of the double infinity values.

By not representing the special values by special objects we avoid the nessessity of having to check for NaN (and the others). On the other hand we have to check for them on comparison operations to stay consistent with the Java Language Specification. Depending on the usage scenario either way could prove better or worse than the other.
